NAME
     sleep - Suspends execution for an interval

SYNOPSIS
     sleep time

DESCRIPTION
   Purpose
     The sleep command suspends execution for time seconds.

EXAMPLES
     The following example allows you continuous use of the shell
     during the ten minutes of delayed execution of the cat(1)
     command:

          (sleep 600; cat sample/a) &

     The following example executes a command periodically:

          while true
          do
               command
               sleep 37
          done

SEE ALSO
     alarm(2), sleep(3C).

NOTES
     The time argument must be less than 65536 seconds.


